<p>
<li><b>Subquadtratic nonobtuse triangulation of convex polygons</b>.<br>
D. Eppstein.<br>
<a href="tr.html">Tech. Rep. 91-61</a>, ICS, UCI, 1991.
<p>
This was merged into "<a href="p-nolarge.html">triangulating polygons
without large angles</a>".
We find a grid-like structure in the input polygon,
which is then thinned out using a complicated divide-and-conquer scheme.
The results are largely subsumed by the method of Bern et al.
described in "<a href="p-cpack.html">Faster circle packing</a>".
